@startuml Validation Sequence Diagram

title CIMUtil - CIM/XML Instance & Profile Validation Sequence

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "Validation\nBuildlet\n[CIMToolPlugin]" as VB #LightSalmon
participant "ValidatorUtil" as VU #LightGreen
participant "RuleParser" as RP #LightBlue
participant "SimpleReasoner\n/ SimpleInfGraph" as SR #LightBlue
participant "ModelValidator\nor SplitValidator" as MV #LightGreen
participant "SplitReader" as SPLIT #LightCoral
participant "Extractor" as EXT #LightBlue
participant "DiagnosisModel\n/ RepairMan" as DM #LightPink
participant "ConsistencyChecks\n[CIMToolPlugin]" as CC #LightSalmon
participant "ProfileValidator" as PV #LightGreen

== Phase 1: Rule Expansion (shared by all validation paths) ==

note over VB, SR
    All three validation paths — CIM/XML instance, split model, and profile consistency —
    begin with the same two-phase rule expansion step in ValidatorUtil.expandRules().
    The schema OntModel is used to resolve namespace prefixes and expand schema-specific
    rule templates before the rules are applied to instance data.
end note

activate VB
VB -> VU : ValidatorUtil.openStandardRules(name)
activate VU
note right of VU
    Loads a bundled .rules file from the
    classpath as an InputStream:
    - "cimtool-simple"  - single CIM/XML file
    - "cimtool-split"   - split model dataset
    - "cimtool-inc"     - incremental split validation
    Rule files use CIMTool's triple-pattern
    rule language (parsed by RuleParser).
end note
VU --> VB : InputStream (rules text)
deactivate VU

VB -> VU : ValidatorUtil.expandRules(schema, ruleText, registry)
activate VU

VU -> RP : new RuleParser(ruleText, registry)
activate RP
note right of RP
    Lexes and parses the rule language.
    Registers the CIM topology namespace
    prefix (guessed from the schema OntModel)
    so rules can reference topology properties
    without hard-coded URIs.
end note
RP -> RP : parse()
RP --> VU : List<Rule> (initial rules)
deactivate RP

VU -> SR : new SimpleReasoner(rules)
activate SR
note right of SR
    CIMTool's custom Jena Reasoner
    implementation (not Jena's built-in
    OWL/RDFS reasoners). Wraps the parsed
    rule list and implements the Jena
    Reasoner interface.
end note
SR --> VU
VU -> SR : bind(schema graph)
activate SR
note right of SR
    Binds the schema graph to produce a
    SimpleInfGraph. Calling prepare() fires
    Stage 1 forward-chaining: schema triples
    are used to specialise generic rule
    templates into schema-specific backward-
    chaining rules (brules). For example,
    a generic "check domain" rule expands
    into a concrete rule for each OWL
    ObjectProperty in the schema.
end note
SR --> VU : SimpleInfGraph
deactivate SR
VU -> VU : extract expanded brules from deductions
VU --> VB : List<Rule> expanded brules
deactivate SR
deactivate VU

== Path A: CIM/XML Single-File Validation ==

VB -> MV : new ModelValidator(schema, ruleText)
activate MV
note right of MV
    Stores the expanded brules and schema.
    Registered as a ValidatorProtocol so
    it can be called once per instance file
    that triggers a build.
end note
MV --> VB : validator
deactivate MV

VB -> MV : validator.run(source, base, namespace, logger)
activate MV

MV -> MV : read instance file into Jena Model
note right of MV
    Reads the CIM/XML (or Turtle) instance
    document using the appropriate Jena reader.
    The data model is a plain Jena Model
    (not a Kena OntModel) at this stage.
end note

MV -> SR : ModelFactory.createInfModel(reasoner, data)
activate SR
note right of SR
    Creates a Jena InfModel backed by the
    SimpleReasoner and the instance data.
    The reasoner applies the expanded brules
    to the combined schema + instance graph.
end note
SR --> MV : InfModel
deactivate SR

MV -> MV : infModel prepare()
note right of MV
    Triggers forward-chaining: the brules
    fire against the instance triples and
    produce deduction triples representing
    validation problems. Each deduction is
    a LOG.Problem triple:
      _:p rdf:type LOG:Problem
      _:p LOG:hasProblems <instanceResource>
      _:p rdfs:comment "error message"
end note

MV -> MV : result = infModel deductions

MV -> VU : ValidatorUtil.logProblems(logger, deductions graph)
activate VU
note right of VU
    Iterates deductions graph for triples
    with rdf:type = LOG.Problem and logs
    each one via the Logger. In the Eclipse
    build path this creates Eclipse IMarkers
    on the instance file. In CLI this prints
    to stderr.
end note
VU --> MV
deactivate VU

MV --> VB : OntModel (diagnosis graph)
deactivate MV

== Path B: Split Model Validation ==

VB -> MV : new SplitValidator(schema, ruleText)
activate MV
note right of MV
    Same rule expansion as Path A but
    configured with additional options
    for split model topology (e.g. proxy
    node handling via ProxyRegistry).
end note
MV --> VB : validator
deactivate MV

VB -> MV : validator.run(source, base, namespace, logger)
activate MV

MV -> SPLIT : new SplitReader(source)
activate SPLIT
note right of SPLIT
    Locates the partitioned CIM/XML dataset
    on disk using SplitBase's hash-based
    directory structure. Opens each part
    file as it is needed during rule firing.
end note
SPLIT --> MV : SplitReader
deactivate SPLIT

MV -> EXT : new Extractor(GraphAdapter(splitReader),\ntransGraph, brules, functors)
activate EXT
note right of EXT
    Extractor applies the brules to the
    split model graph. It uses an AsyncModel
    interface (backed by SplitReader) to
    stream triples part-by-part rather than
    loading the entire dataset into memory.
    ValidationBuiltins provide built-in
    functor implementations for CIM-specific
    checks (e.g. topology connectivity rules).
end note
EXT -> EXT : run()
EXT --> MV : result graph (deductions)
deactivate EXT

MV -> VU : ValidatorUtil.logProblems(logger, result)
activate VU
VU --> MV
deactivate VU

MV --> VB : OntModel (diagnosis graph)
deactivate MV
deactivate VB

== Path C: Profile Consistency Check ==

activate CC
CC -> PV : new ProfileValidator(profileModel, backgroundModel)
activate PV
note right of PV
    target = the .owl profile OntModel
    reference = the background schema OntModel
    Checks that every class and property
    referenced in the profile is resolvable
    in the schema (the background model).
end note
PV --> CC : checker
deactivate PV

CC -> PV : checker.run()
activate PV

PV -> PV : buildRules()
note right of PV
    Loads the profile-specific rule set
    which checks for dangling references,
    unknown property types, and cardinality
    inconsistencies between the profile
    and its schema.
end note

PV -> SR : TransitiveReasoner bind(reference graph)
activate SR
note right of SR
    Wraps the reference schema graph in
    a transitive inferencer so that
    rdfs:subClassOf / rdfs:subPropertyOf
    chains are resolved during rule matching.
    This is needed for inheritance-aware
    profile consistency checking.
end note
SR --> PV : InfGraph (transitive schema)
deactivate SR

PV -> EXT : new Extractor(GraphAdapter(target),\ntransGraph, rules, functors)
activate EXT
note right of EXT
    Applies profile-validation rules to the
    profile graph, using the transitively-
    reasoned schema as axioms. Violations
    are emitted as LOG.Problem deductions.
end note
EXT -> EXT : run()
EXT --> PV : result graph (log)
deactivate EXT

PV -> PV : log = ModelFactory.createMem(result)
PV --> CC : (checker with log populated)
deactivate PV

alt checker.hasErrors()
    CC -> DM : new DiagnosisModel(new RepairMan())
    activate DM
    note right of DM
        DiagnosisModel wraps the deductions
        graph as a JFace tree model for the
        Eclipse Diagnosis and Repair editors.
        It exposes LOG.Problem nodes as tree
        items grouped by the instance resource
        they apply to (LOG.hasProblems subject).
        RepairMan holds RepairAction entries
        that can apply automatic fixes to the
        profile OWL model when the user
        accepts a repair suggestion.
    end note
    CC -> DM : setRootResource(DIAGNOSIS_ROOT)
    DM --> CC : diagnosisModel (for Repair/Diagnosis editor)
    deactivate DM
    CC -> CC : write log to .repair file\nCIMBuilder.addMarker(file, message)
end

deactivate CC

@enduml
